Never heard of bakedeath before but I went ahead and watched it and at first I was put off by her tone of voice because I thought it didn't match the song but then she started fluctuating her voice, and that's when I started liking it. 

On top of that, when the small growls came in, it was over for me from there. Head bops needed to be delivered pronto. She also incorperated a lot of the noisiness from the original song which was definitely well-edited and added more creepiness to the cover in contrast to Bae's cleaner version where pure vocals were the main focus of the cover.

I still prefer Bae's version but that's purely based on bias because I liked Bae's stylistic choice of adding the breathiness and vocal frys to her singing(which makes her sound like a zombie) but in terms of quality, I think bakedeath got it in the bag, it sounded super professional.
